#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn35.155"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.155:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.155:0.2"
msgid "15. Navapurāṇavagga "
msgstr "15. The Old and the New "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 155. Dhammakathikapucchasutta → kammakathikasuttaṃ (bj) | kathika (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.155:0.3"
msgid "155. Dhammakathikapucchasutta "
msgstr "155. A Dhamma Speaker "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.141, sc1
msgctxt "sn35.155:1.1"
msgid "Atha kho aññataro bhikkhu yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami … pe … ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so bhikkhu bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then a mendicant went up to the Buddha … and asked him, "

msgctxt "sn35.155:1.2"
msgid "“‘dhammakathiko, dhammakathiko’ti, bhante, vuccati. "
msgstr "“Sir, they speak of a ‘Dhamma speaker’. "

msgctxt "sn35.155:1.3"
msgid "Kittāvatā nu kho, bhante, dhammakathiko hotī”ti? "
msgstr "How is a Dhamma speaker defined?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn35.155:2.1"
msgid "“Cakkhussa ce, bhikkhu, nibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya dhammaṃ deseti, ‘dhammakathiko bhikkhū’ti alaṃvacanāya. "
msgstr "“If a mendicant teaches Dhamma for disillusionment, dispassion, and cessation regarding the eye, they’re qualified to be called a ‘mendicant who speaks on Dhamma’. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.155:2.2"
msgid "Cakkhussa ce, bhikkhu, nibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya paṭipanno hoti, ‘dhammānudhammappaṭipanno bhikkhū’ti alaṃvacanāya. "
msgstr "If they practice for disillusionment, dispassion, and cessation regarding the eye, they’re qualified to be called a ‘mendicant who practices in line with the teaching’. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.155:2.3"
msgid "Cakkhussa ce, bhikkhu, nibbidā virāgā nirodhā anupādāvimutto hoti, ‘diṭṭhadhammanibbānappatto bhikkhū’ti alaṃvacanāya … pe … "
msgstr "If they’re freed by not grasping by disillusionment, dispassion, and cessation regarding the eye, they’re qualified to be called a ‘mendicant who has attained extinguishment in this very life’. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.155:2.4"
msgid "jivhāya ce, bhikkhu, nibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya dhammaṃ deseti, ‘dhammakathiko bhikkhū’ti alaṃvacanāya … pe … "
msgstr "If a mendicant teaches Dhamma for disillusionment with the ear … nose … tongue … body … "

msgctxt "sn35.155:2.5"
msgid "manassa ce, bhikkhu, nibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya dhammaṃ deseti, ‘dhammakathiko bhikkhū’ti alaṃvacanāya. "
msgstr "mind, for its fading away and cessation, they’re qualified to be called a ‘mendicant who speaks on Dhamma’. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.155:2.6"
msgid "Manassa ce, bhikkhu, nibbidāya virāgāya nirodhāya paṭipanno hoti, ‘dhammānudhammappaṭipanno bhikkhū’ti alaṃvacanāya. "
msgstr "If they practice for disillusionment, dispassion, and cessation regarding the mind, they’re qualified to be called a ‘mendicant who practices in line with the teaching’. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.155:2.7"
msgid "Manassa ce, bhikkhu, nibbidā virāgā nirodhā anupādāvimutto hoti, ‘diṭṭhadhammanibbānappatto bhikkhū’ti alaṃvacanāyā”ti. "
msgstr "If they’re freed by not grasping by disillusionment, dispassion, and cessation regarding the mind, they’re qualified to be called a ‘mendicant who has attained extinguishment in this very life’.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.155:2.8"
msgid "Dasamaṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.155:2.9"
msgid "Navapurāṇavaggo pañcamo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn35.155:3.1"
msgid "Kammaṃ cattāri sappāyā, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn35.155:3.2"
msgid "anantevāsi kimatthiyā; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn35.155:3.3"
msgid "Atthi nu kho pariyāyo, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn35.155:3.4"
msgid "indriyakathikena cāti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.155:3.5"
msgid "Saḷāyatanavagge tatiyapaṇṇāsako samatto. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="vagguddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn35.155:4.1"
msgid "Yogakkhemi ca loko ca, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn35.155:4.2"
msgid "Gahapati devadahena ca; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn35.155:4.3"
msgid "Navapurāṇena paṇṇāso, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn35.155:4.4"
msgid "Tatiyo tena vuccatīti. "
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
